Errors found:
  my - Sentences should start with a capital letter.
  are - Subject-verb agreement: "battery" is singular and requires "is" not "are".
  it - Use "its" (possessive) to show ownership, not "it".
  buy - Verb tense: Use "bought" (past tense) for completed actions.
  drain - Use "draining" (present participle) with "are" for ongoing action.
